{"id":"aba-zca.2","title":"Phase 1: Core Types & SQLite Schema","description":"## What

Design and implement the SQLite database schema for the Abacus application graph, including all table definitions, indexes, FTS5 virtual tables, and the TypeScript type system that maps to it. Also implement the DB connection module with WAL mode, migrations, and prepared statement management.

## Context

The graph uses an adjacency list model with two core tables (nodes + edges) plus FTS5 for full-text search. All node types (Route, Entity, Page, Action, Permission) share the same nodes table differentiated by a \`kind\` column, with type-specific data in a JSONB \`properties\` column.

Research findings:
- Use JSONB (not TEXT JSON) for properties — 20x faster for repeated operations (SQLite 3.45+)
- Use generated virtual columns for frequently-queried JSON fields (file_path, method, etc.) to enable indexing
- WAL mode for concurrent reads, NORMAL synchronous for CLI speed
- FTS5 with BM25 ranking for fuzzy matching
- better-sqlite3 synchronous API — no async needed

## Implementation

### SQLite Schema (DDL)
\`\`\`sql
-- Core graph tables
CREATE TABLE nodes (
  id          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  kind        TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(kind IN ('route', 'entity', 'page', 'action', 'permission')),
  name        TEXT NOT NULL,
  label       TEXT NOT NULL,          -- human-readable display name
  properties  BLOB,                   -- JSONB metadata
  source      TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(source IN ('scan', 'agent', 'manual')),
  source_file TEXT,                   -- file path this was scanned from
  created_at  INTEGER DEFAULT (unixepoch()),
  updated_at  INTEGER DEFAULT (unixepoch()),
  scan_hash   TEXT                    -- hash of source content for change detection
);

CREATE TABLE edges (
  id          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  src_id      TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES nodes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  dst_id      TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES nodes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  kind        TEXT NOT NULL,          -- 'uses_route', 'touches_entity', 'on_page', 'requires_permission', 'relates_to', 'field_relation'
  properties  BLOB,                   -- JSONB edge metadata
  created_at  INTEGER DEFAULT (unixepoch()),
  UNIQUE(src_id, dst_id, kind)
);

-- Indexes for traversal
CREATE INDEX idx_nodes_kind ON nodes(kind);
CREATE INDEX idx_nodes_name ON nodes(name);
CREATE INDEX idx_edges_src ON edges(src_id, kind);
CREATE INDEX idx_edges_dst ON edges(dst_id, kind);

-- Generated virtual columns for Route-specific indexed queries
-- (SQLite evaluates these lazily — no storage cost)

-- FTS5 for full-text search across node names and labels
CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE nodes_fts USING fts5(
  name,
  label,
  content,
  content=nodes,
  content_rowid=rowid,
  tokenize='porter unicode61'
);

-- Triggers to keep FTS in sync
CREATE TRIGGER nodes_ai AFTER INSERT ON nodes BEGIN
  INSERT INTO nodes_fts(rowid, name, label, content)
  VALUES (new.rowid, new.name, new.label, '');
END;

CREATE TRIGGER nodes_ad AFTER DELETE ON nodes BEGIN
  INSERT INTO nodes_fts(nodes_fts, rowid, name, label, content)
  VALUES ('delete', old.rowid, old.name, old.label, '');
END;

CREATE TRIGGER nodes_au AFTER UPDATE ON nodes BEGIN
  INSERT INTO nodes_fts(nodes_fts, rowid, name, label, content)
  VALUES ('delete', old.rowid, old.name, old.label, '');
  INSERT INTO nodes_fts(rowid, name, label, content)
  VALUES (new.rowid, new.name, new.label, '');
END;

-- Schema version tracking
CREATE TABLE schema_version (
  version INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  applied_at INTEGER DEFAULT (unixepoch())
);
INSERT INTO schema_version (version) VALUES (1);
\`\`\`

### TypeScript Types (packages/core/src/types.ts)

\`\`\`typescript
// Node kinds
export type NodeKind = 'route' | 'entity' | 'page' | 'action' | 'permission';
export type NodeSource = 'scan' | 'agent' | 'manual';
export type EdgeKind = 'uses_route' | 'touches_entity' | 'on_page' | 'requires_permission' | 'relates_to' | 'field_relation';

// Base node
export interface GraphNode {
  id: string;
  kind: NodeKind;
  name: string;
  label: string;
  properties: Record<string, unknown>;
  source: NodeSource;
  source_file: string | null;
  created_at: number;
  updated_at: number;
  scan_hash: string | null;
}

// Route properties
export interface RouteProperties {
  method: string;          // GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH
  path: string;            // /api/auth/register
  summary?: string;
  tags?: string[];
  inputSchema?: unknown;   // JSON Schema representation
  outputSchema?: unknown;
  successStatus?: number;
  contractFile: string;    // source file path
  handlerFile?: string;
}

// Entity properties
export interface EntityProperties {
  fields: EntityField[];
  relations: EntityRelation[];
  tableName?: string;
  schemaFile: string;
}

export interface EntityField {
  name: string;
  type: string;
  isRequired: boolean;
  isId: boolean;
  isUnique: boolean;
  default?: string;
}

export interface EntityRelation {
  name: string;
  type: 'one-to-one' | 'one-to-many' | 'many-to-many';
  targetEntity: string;
  foreignKey?: string;
}

// Page properties
export interface PageProperties {
  urlPattern: string;      // /jobs/:id
  component: string;       // JobDetail
  componentFile?: string;
  isProtected: boolean;
  parentRoute?: string;
  layoutComponent?: string;
}

// Action properties (the semantic bridge)
export interface ActionProperties {
  description: string;
  gherkinPatterns: string[];     // Cucumber expression patterns
  apiRoute?: string;             // node ID of associated Route
  entities: string[];            // node IDs of associated Entities
  page?: string;                 // node ID of associated Page
  permissions: string[];         // permission strings or node IDs
  uiHints?: Record<string, string>; // testId, formSelector, etc.
  preconditions?: string[];      // setup requirements for this action
  postconditions?: string[];     // expected state after action
}

// Permission properties
export interface PermissionProperties {
  resource: string;
  operation: string;     // read, write, delete, admin
  roles?: string[];
  aclSource?: string;    // file where ACL is defined
}

// Edge
export interface GraphEdge {
  id: string;
  src_id: string;
  dst_id: string;
  kind: EdgeKind;
  properties: Record<string, unknown>;
  created_at: number;
}
\`\`\`

### DB Connection Module (packages/core/src/db.ts)

- openDb(path: string) — opens/creates DB with WAL mode, cache, foreign keys
- initSchema(db) — runs DDL if tables don't exist, handles migrations
- closeDb(db) — graceful close
- Prepared statement cache — lazy-init Map<string, Statement>
- Transaction helpers — wrap better-sqlite3 transaction()
- Generate IDs: \`{kind}:{name}\` format (e.g., "route:post-/api/auth/register", "entity:User")

## Testing

- [ ] openDb creates a new database file with correct pragmas (WAL, foreign_keys, cache_size)
- [ ] initSchema creates all tables, indexes, triggers, and FTS5 virtual table
- [ ] Node CRUD: insert, read, update, delete with cascading edge deletion
- [ ] Edge CRUD: insert with UNIQUE constraint enforcement
- [ ] FTS5 search returns results ranked by BM25
- [ ] FTS5 triggers fire on insert, update, delete — FTS stays in sync
- [ ] JSONB properties round-trip correctly (store and retrieve complex objects)
- [ ] Generated virtual columns are queryable and indexed
- [ ] Schema version tracking works (migration path for future changes)
- [ ] Concurrent reads work (WAL mode)
- [ ] Transaction rollback on error
- [ ] ID generation is deterministic and collision-free

## Validation

- [ ] All 5 node types can be stored and retrieved with full properties
- [ ] Edges correctly link nodes with referential integrity
- [ ] FTS5 search returns relevant results for partial name matches
- [ ] Schema migrations are forward-compatible
- [ ] Database file size is reasonable for 200+ nodes

## Files

- packages/core/src/types.ts
- packages/core/src/db.ts
- packages/core/src/schema.sql (or embedded in db.ts)
- packages/core/src/__tests__/db.test.ts
- packages/core/src/__tests__/types.test.ts

## Dependencies

