{"id":"aba-zca.7","title":"Phase 3: Graph Query Layer","description":"## What

Implement the graph query layer that provides CRUD operations for all node types, edge management, full-text search, and graph traversal queries. This is the core data access layer that CLI commands and MCP tools call.

## Context

The query layer sits between the SQLite database (db.ts) and the consumers (CLI, MCP server). It provides a typed, high-level API for interacting with the graph. All queries use better-sqlite3 prepared statements for performance.

Key design principles:
- All methods are synchronous (better-sqlite3 is sync)
- Bulk operations use transactions for atomicity and performance
- FTS5 queries use BM25 ranking
- Graph traversal uses recursive CTEs
- Results are typed using the core type system

## Implementation

### Graph Repository (packages/core/src/graph/repository.ts)

\`\`\`typescript
export class GraphRepository {
  constructor(private db: Database.Database) {}

  // === Node Operations ===
  insertNode(node: Omit<GraphNode, 'created_at' | 'updated_at'>): GraphNode;
  upsertNode(node: Omit<GraphNode, 'created_at' | 'updated_at'>): GraphNode;
  getNode(id: string): GraphNode | null;
  getNodesByKind(kind: NodeKind, options?: { limit?: number; offset?: number }): GraphNode[];
  deleteNode(id: string): boolean;  // cascades to edges
  deleteNodesBySource(source: NodeSource, scannerIds?: string[]): number;

  // === Edge Operations ===
  insertEdge(edge: Omit<GraphEdge, 'created_at'>): GraphEdge;
  getEdgesFrom(nodeId: string, kind?: EdgeKind): GraphEdge[];
  getEdgesTo(nodeId: string, kind?: EdgeKind): GraphEdge[];
  deleteEdge(id: string): boolean;

  // === Search ===
  search(query: string, options?: { kind?: NodeKind; limit?: number }): SearchResult[];
  searchByName(pattern: string, kind?: NodeKind): GraphNode[];

  // === Graph Traversal ===
  getConnected(nodeId: string, maxDepth?: number): SubGraph;
  getRelated(nodeId: string): GraphNode[];  // all nodes connected by any edge

  // === Bulk Operations (transactional) ===
  bulkUpsertNodes(nodes: Omit<GraphNode, 'created_at' | 'updated_at'>[]): number;
  bulkInsertEdges(edges: Omit<GraphEdge, 'created_at'>[]): number;

  // === Scan Sync ===
  syncScanResults(scanResult: ScanResult): SyncReport;
  // Upserts nodes from scan, removes nodes no longer in scan results,
  // reports: added, updated, removed, unchanged
}

export interface SearchResult {
  node: GraphNode;
  rank: number;           // BM25 score
  highlights: string[];   // highlighted match context
}

export interface SubGraph {
  nodes: GraphNode[];
  edges: GraphEdge[];
}

export interface SyncReport {
  added: number;
  updated: number;
  removed: number;
  unchanged: number;
  staleActions: string[];  // Action IDs referencing removed nodes
}
\`\`\`

### Key Implementation Details

**syncScanResults** is the most complex method — it must:
1. Get all existing scan-sourced nodes for the scanner's node kinds
2. Compare incoming nodes against existing by ID
3. Upsert new/changed nodes (using scan_hash for change detection)
4. Delete nodes that exist in DB but not in scan results
5. Check if any Actions reference deleted nodes → return as staleActions
6. All in a single transaction

**getConnected** uses recursive CTE:
\`\`\`sql
WITH RECURSIVE connected(node_id, depth) AS (
  SELECT :startId, 0
  UNION ALL
  SELECT CASE WHEN e.src_id = c.node_id THEN e.dst_id ELSE e.src_id END, c.depth + 1
  FROM (SELECT * FROM edges UNION ALL SELECT id, dst_id, src_id, kind, properties, created_at FROM edges) e
  JOIN connected c ON (e.src_id = c.node_id OR e.dst_id = c.node_id)
  WHERE c.depth < :maxDepth
)
SELECT DISTINCT n.* FROM connected c JOIN nodes n ON n.id = c.node_id
\`\`\`

## Testing

- [ ] insertNode creates node and returns it with timestamps
- [ ] upsertNode creates new node if not exists
- [ ] upsertNode updates existing node, changes updated_at
- [ ] getNode returns null for nonexistent ID
- [ ] getNodesByKind filters correctly and supports pagination
- [ ] deleteNode removes node and cascades to edges
- [ ] insertEdge enforces UNIQUE(src_id, dst_id, kind)
- [ ] getEdgesFrom/getEdgesTo return correct directional edges
- [ ] search returns FTS5 results ranked by BM25
- [ ] search filters by kind when specified
- [ ] searchByName uses LIKE pattern matching
- [ ] getConnected traverses graph up to maxDepth
- [ ] getConnected handles cycles without infinite loop
- [ ] bulkUpsertNodes is transactional — all or nothing
- [ ] syncScanResults correctly adds, updates, removes nodes
- [ ] syncScanResults detects stale Actions
- [ ] syncScanResults uses scan_hash to skip unchanged nodes

## Validation

- [ ] All CRUD operations work for all 5 node types
- [ ] Edge referential integrity is maintained
- [ ] FTS5 search returns relevant results
- [ ] Graph traversal returns correct subgraphs
- [ ] Sync operation is idempotent (running twice with same data = no changes)
- [ ] Performance: bulk insert of 200 nodes completes in < 100ms

## Files

- packages/core/src/graph/repository.ts
- packages/core/src/graph/index.ts (re-exports)
- packages/core/src/__tests__/graph/repository.test.ts

## Dependencies

