{"id":"aba-zca.8","title":"Phase 3: Action CRUD & Enrichment Protocol","description":"## What

Implement the Action node management layer — creating, reading, updating, and deleting Actions (the semantic bridge between Gherkin steps and technical nodes). This includes validation against the graph, enrichment helpers, and the protocol for how agents add Actions.

## Context

Actions are the heart of Abacus. They bridge human-readable Gherkin step text to technical implementation details (Routes, Entities, Pages, Permissions). Unlike structural nodes (auto-scanned), Actions are created by agents or humans as they work through features.

Key properties of an Action:
- gherkinPatterns: string[] — Cucumber expression patterns this Action matches
- apiRoute: string — reference to a Route node ID
- entities: string[] — references to Entity node IDs
- page: string — reference to a Page node ID
- permissions: string[] — permission strings
- uiHints: { testId, formSelector, etc. }
- preconditions/postconditions — setup and expected state

### Agent Enrichment Protocol
When an agent works on a feature:
1. Agent queries for matching Actions (via match layer — next bead)
2. If match found → agent uses the Action's context
3. If no match → agent creates a new Action by:
   a. Identifying the relevant Route(s) from the graph
   b. Identifying the relevant Entity(ies)
   c. Identifying the Page where this action happens
   d. Composing a Gherkin pattern for this action
   e. Calling Action create with all references
4. The new Action persists → future agents can find it

### Validation Rules
- apiRoute reference must point to an existing Route node (or be null)
- entity references must point to existing Entity nodes (warn if not found)
- page reference must point to an existing Page node (or be null)
- gherkinPatterns must be valid Cucumber expressions (parseable)
- Action name must be unique

## Implementation

### ActionService (packages/core/src/graph/actions.ts)

\`\`\`typescript
export class ActionService {
  constructor(private repo: GraphRepository) {}

  /** Create a new Action node with validation */
  create(input: CreateActionInput): ActionResult;

  /** Update an existing Action (merge gherkinPatterns, update references) */
  update(id: string, input: UpdateActionInput): ActionResult;

  /** Get an Action by ID */
  get(id: string): ActionNode | null;

  /** List all Actions, optionally filtered */
  list(options?: { tag?: string; route?: string; entity?: string }): ActionNode[];

  /** Delete an Action */
  delete(id: string): boolean;

  /** Suggest Actions for a given context (route + entity combination) */
  suggest(context: { route?: string; entity?: string; page?: string }): ActionNode[];

  /** Validate all Actions against current graph (find stale references) */
  audit(): ActionAudit;
}

export interface CreateActionInput {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  gherkinPatterns: string[];
  apiRoute?: string;      // Route node ID
  entities?: string[];    // Entity node IDs
  page?: string;          // Page node ID
  permissions?: string[];
  uiHints?: Record<string, string>;
  preconditions?: string[];
  postconditions?: string[];
}

export interface ActionResult {
  success: boolean;
  action?: ActionNode;
  warnings: string[];     // e.g., "Entity 'entity:Foo' not found in graph"
  errors: string[];       // e.g., "Invalid Cucumber expression: ..."
}

export interface ActionNode extends GraphNode {
  properties: ActionProperties;
  // Resolved references (populated by service)
  resolvedRoute?: GraphNode;
  resolvedEntities?: GraphNode[];
  resolvedPage?: GraphNode;
}

export interface ActionAudit {
  total: number;
  valid: number;
  stale: ActionAuditItem[];   // Actions with broken references
}
\`\`\`

### Cucumber Expression Validation
Use @cucumber/cucumber-expressions to validate patterns:
\`\`\`typescript
import { CucumberExpressionGenerator, ParameterTypeRegistry } from '@cucumber/cucumber-expressions';
\`\`\`

## Testing

- [ ] Create Action with valid references → success
- [ ] Create Action with invalid Route reference → warning (not error — route may be added later)
- [ ] Create Action with invalid Cucumber expression → error
- [ ] Create Action with duplicate name → error
- [ ] Update Action merges new gherkinPatterns with existing ones
- [ ] Update Action replaces apiRoute reference
- [ ] Get Action returns null for nonexistent ID
- [ ] Get Action resolves references (populates resolvedRoute, resolvedEntities)
- [ ] List Actions filters by tag, route, entity
- [ ] Delete Action removes node and all edges
- [ ] Suggest Actions finds Actions related to given route/entity context
- [ ] Audit detects stale references (Actions pointing to deleted nodes)
- [ ] Audit reports valid vs stale counts
- [ ] Multiple gherkinPatterns (aliases) work — Action matches on any pattern

## Validation

- [ ] Full CRUD lifecycle works: create → read → update → delete
- [ ] Validation catches invalid inputs with clear error messages
- [ ] Reference resolution correctly joins to Route/Entity/Page nodes
- [ ] Audit correctly identifies broken references after scan removes nodes
- [ ] Action creation creates appropriate edges (uses_route, touches_entity, on_page)

## Files

- packages/core/src/graph/actions.ts
- packages/core/src/__tests__/graph/actions.test.ts

## Dependencies

